  <title>Clutter.Container::actor-added</title>
<synopsis><code mime="text/x-python">
def callback(container, actor, user_param1, ...)
</code></synopsis>
<p>The ::actor-added signal is emitted each time an actor
has been added to @container.</p>

<table>
<tr>
<td><p>container :</p></td>
<td><p>instance of Clutter.Container that is emitting the signal</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p>actor :</p></td>
<td><p>the new child that has been added to @container</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p>user_param1 :</p></td>
<td><p>first user parameter (if any) specified with the connect() method</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p>... :</p></td>
<td><p>additional user parameters (if any)</p></td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>Since 0.4</p>
